# feat/fix/docs/style/refactor/perf/test/ci/chore/revert/ops
#
# 1. Use 'chore' for tool changes, configuration changes, and changes
# to things that do not actually go into production at all
#
# 2. append '!' for a breaking change
# and include a 'BREAKING CHANGE' footer. For example:
#
# ---
#
# > chore!: [TICKET] drop support for Node 6
#
# > BREAKING CHANGE: use JavaScript features not available in Node 6.
#
# ---
#
# 3. Add references in the footer:
#
# ---
#
# > fix: [TICKET] prevent racing of requests
#
# > Introduce a request id and a reference to latest request.
#
# > Refs: #123
#
# ---
#
# Based on https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/
